    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#paci2011"/>, p. <citedRange>268</citedRange> and fig. 14.1.8 and fig. 8</bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>61.1555.B.1</citedRange></bibl> and 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>61.1555.B.2</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>115500</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#gasparini-rosamilia2016"/>, pp. <citedRange>190-195</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>66.2322</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Ἀντίπατρος"><seg part="I">Ἀντιπα<supplied reason="lost">τρ</supplied></seg><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name></persName>
                </ab></div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Antipatros  <note>ou</note> d'Antipatros.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Antipatros <note>or </note> belonging to Antipatros.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Antipatros <note>o</note> di Antipatros.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>One of the series of personal names inscribed above altars rock-cut in niches; the 'owner' of the altar(s) engraved his name, but we
                do not know the deity to whom offerings were laid down.</p>
                <p>Neither do we know whether the personal name was written at the nominative or genitive case.</p>
                <p>Paci's description was misinterpreted in SEG, producing two similar items. The name <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἀντίπα[τρος]</foreign> is engraved 
                    only once across two niches.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
